_header: I am beginning and end that made each creature
Subjects: Arthur, prince of Wales; Catherine of Aragon; pageant verses; occasional verse
_description: Speech of the Father of Heaven at the Pageant celebrating the marriage of Prince Arthur to Princess Catherine — four stanzas rhyme royal

BLCottVitAXVI.First Lines: I am begynnyng & ende that made eche creatureMy self & for my self but man especially…
BLCottVitAXVI.Last Lines: …Your Rebellious Enemyes I shall put in your handEncreasyng in honour both you & your land
